modules.description: This module defines a variant type for representing Redis replies in the Redis Serialization Protocol (RESP), including atomic values like integers, strings, and statuses, as well as composite types like arrays and hash tables. It provides constructors for building RESP values and safe extraction functions for interpreting them, with explicit handling of nil and error states. It is used to process and construct raw Redis responses in a type-safe manner, particularly when parsing network data or building Redis clients.
